The paper discusses the use of information compression and search in various aspects of computing and cognition, including natural language processing, pattern recognition, and probabilistic reasoning. These topics are commonly associated with the sub-categories of artificial intelligence (cs.AI), computational linguistics (cs.CL), machine learning (cs.LG), information theory (cs.IT), and data structures and algorithms (cs.DS).
